	<div class="container">
		<div class="project-hero__content">
			
			<h1 class="project-hero__title">Californians aren&#8217;t getting the mental health care they&#8217;re legally guaranteed. Why not?</h1>

			
						<p class="project-hero__intro">Laws require health plans to provide patients equal treatment for mental and physical needs. But &quot;parity&quot; is often elusive — and critics say the Legislature and health officials have failed to fix the problem.</p>
			
							<div class="project-hero__caption">

											<svg role="img" class="icon icon--camera" aria-label="camera"><use xlink:href="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/themes/thenewsproject/dist/svg/dist/symbol/svg/sprite.symbol.svg#camera"></use></svg>						<span>Sen. Jim Beall exits the senate floor on September 4, 2019. Photo by Anne Wernikoff for CalMatters</span>
									</div>
					</div>
	</div>
</div>

